---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Base title="Reasoning & Recovery | Enhanced Task Completion">
  <article class="scenario">
    <div class="container">
      <a href={base} class="back">&larr; All scenarios</a>

      <header class="scenario__header">
        <span class="badge badge--primary">Adaptive Reasoning</span>
        <h1>Reasoning & Recovery</h1>
        <p class="scenario__lead">
          The agent handles errors and unexpected tool results gracefully — reasoning about failures,
          explaining them clearly to the user, and suggesting practical next steps.
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Screenshot -->
      <div class="scenario__screenshot">
        <img src={`${base}images/scenario-reasoning.png`} alt="Adaptive reasoning and error recovery in the Gradio chat UI" />
      </div>

      <!-- What happens -->
      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>What happens</h2>
        <p>When the user asks <em>"Can you check where my Kindle delivery is right now?"</em>, the agent:</p>

        <ol class="scenario__steps">
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x1F50D;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Calls <code>search_orders</code> to find the Kindle order</strong>
                <p>Locates the user's Kindle order and retrieves its order ID for further lookup.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x1F4E6;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Calls <code>get_shipment</code> for tracking details</strong>
                <p>Attempts to retrieve shipping and tracking information for the order.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x26A0;&#xFE0F;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Receives an error — order still processing, no tracking yet</strong>
                <p>The tool returns an error indicating the order hasn't shipped yet, so no tracking number or carrier information exists.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x1F9E0;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Reasons about the failure</strong>
                <p>Instead of showing a raw error, the agent interprets it: the order is still being processed, shipping hasn't started, and this is a normal state — not a problem.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x2705;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Explains clearly and suggests next steps</strong>
                <p>Tells the user their order hasn't shipped yet, explains the current processing status, and suggests watching for a shipping confirmation email with tracking details.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- Why it matters -->
      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>Why it matters</h2>
        <div class="value-grid">
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Graceful error handling</h3>
            <p>Tool errors don't crash the conversation. The agent catches failures, understands their meaning, and continues helping the user instead of giving up.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Transparent reasoning</h3>
            <p>The agent explains <em>why</em> something failed — not just <em>that</em> it failed — so the user understands the situation without needing technical knowledge.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>User-friendly error explanation</h3>
            <p>Raw API errors become plain-language explanations with actionable suggestions, turning a dead end into a helpful interaction.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Try it -->
      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>Try it yourself</h2>
        <div class="try-prompt">
          <p class="try-prompt__label">Copy this prompt:</p>
          <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">
            I'm Emily Chen. I returned a damaged Blu-ray disc a couple weeks ago — can you check if my refund has been processed yet, and also tell me where my ergonomic chair delivery is right now?
          </blockquote>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .scenario {
    padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
  }
  .back {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--c-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }
  .back:hover { color: var(--c-primary); }

  .scenario__header {
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  .scenario__header h1 {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }
  .scenario__lead {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--c-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .scenario__screenshot {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }
  .scenario__screenshot img {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .scenario__section {
    margin-top: var(--space-3xl);
  }
  .scenario__section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .scenario__section > p {
    color: var(--c-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .scenario__steps {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }
  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--c-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .step:hover { border-color: var(--c-border); }
  .step__icon {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .step__content strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 2px;
  }
  .step__content p {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--c-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .value-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .value-card {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--c-surface-raised);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }
  .value-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }
  .value-card p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--c-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .try-prompt {
    background: var(--c-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .try-prompt__label {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--c-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }
  .try-prompt__text {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--c-text);
    line-height: 1.65;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--c-primary);
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
